        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Purple ... - \"Purple, crimson, and blue,\" would be needed for the hangings of the temple, which, in this respect, as in others, was conformed to the pattern of the tabernacle (see Exodus 25:4; Exodus 26:1, etc.). Hiram's power of \"working in purple, crimson,\" etc., was probably a knowledge of the best modes of dyeing cloth these colors. The Phoenicians, off whose coast the murex was commonly taken, were famous as purple dyers from a very remote period.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Purple ... - \"Purple, crimson, and blue,\" would be needed for the hangings of the temple, which, in this respect, as in others, was conformed to the pattern of the tabernacle (see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
