            "text": ", etc.). Hiram's power of \"working in purple, crimson,\" etc., was probably a knowledge of the best modes of dyeing cloth these colors. The Phoenicians, off whose coast the murex was commonly taken, were famous as purple dyers from a very remote period.",
            "children": []
